00:02:25.780 --> 00:02:30.100
The beets look like they're heating and
thickening well, and OH!, and they smell delicious!

00:02:30.100 --> 00:02:35.920
One way that I can tell they
are done is run my finger over the back

00:02:35.920 --> 00:02:39.819
of the spoon and if the sauce does not
run together, it's done.

00:02:42.160 --> 00:02:46.600
And they are ready and you can see where
the sauce is already starting to thicken.

00:02:46.600 --> 00:02:52.210
I have seen some add a hint of clove or
some orange juice or zest.

00:02:52.210 --> 00:02:56.740
I like the traditional version. You can
store these Harvard beets in the

00:02:56.740 --> 00:03:01.780
refrigerator up to a week. Just add a
little bit of water and reheat over

00:03:01.780 --> 00:03:03.220
medium heat.

00:03:03.220 --> 00:03:08.170
I hope you give this Harvard beet recipe
a try. Being that the beets are so rich

00:03:08.170 --> 00:03:12.520
and creamy, sweet and good, it is a good
way to get the kids to eat their vegetables.

